ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Who goes to more parties, you or others?
Notes: 1=I go to many fewer parties than others do; 2=I go to fewer parties than others do; 3=I go to as many parties as others do; 4=I go to more parties than others do; 5=I go to many more parties than others do; -5=Item seen but not answered; -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=Data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)

ElementDescription: Who has more friends, you or others?
Notes: 1=I have many fewer friends than others do; 2=I have fewer friends than others do; 3=I have about as many friends as others do; 4=I have more friends than others do; 5=I have many more friends than others do; -5=Item seen but not answered; -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=Data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)

ElementDescription: Who dines out more, you or others?
Notes: 1=I dine out much less than others do; 2=I dine out less than others do; 3=I dine out about as much as others do; 4=I dine out more than others do; 5=I dine out much more than others do; -5=Item seen but not answered;  -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)

ElementDescription: Who is a part of a greater number of social circles, you or others?
Notes: 1=I am a part of many fewer distinct social circles than others are; 2=I am a part of fewer distinct social circles than others are; 3=I am a part of about as many distinct social circles as others are; 4=I am a part of more distinct social circles than others are; 5=I am a part of many more distinct social circles than others are; -5=Item seen but not answered;  -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=Data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)

ElementDescription: Who sees and interacts with their extended family more, you or others?
Notes: 1=I see and interact with extended family much less than others do; 2=I see and interact with extended family less than others do; 3=I see and interact with extended family about as much as others do; 4=I see and interact with extended family more than others do; 5=I see and interact with extended family much more than others do; -5=Item seen but not answered; -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=Data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)

ElementDescription: Who has a wider social network, you or others?
Notes: 1=I have a much less wide social network than others do; 2=I have a less wide social network than others do; 3=I have about as wide social network as others do; 4=I have a wider social network than others do; 5=I have a much more wide social network than others do; -5=Item seen but not answered; -9=Item hidden by show-if logic; -999=Data not submitted (not seen, incomplete)
